	it's due

2003-04-28 13:20  Josef Spillner <dr_maux@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/ggz-config.c: - Fixes to ggz-config:	* when removing
	invalid sections, remove them completely, so we don't get an   
	error about an unexisting section when running with --check the
	next time  * don't crash if section key is NULL (which it is after
	we deleted it)	* when validating CommandLine entries, disregard
	all options, check only for    the correct filename

2003-03-29 21:38  Josef Spillner <dr_maux@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: netxml.c, server.c: - use h_errno value and herrstr()
	when host lookup failures occur
	
	When connecting to unknown hosts, instead of 'Success' one should
	now see 'Unknown host'

2003-03-29 11:31  Josef Spillner <dr_maux@users.sourceforge.net>

	* autogen.sh: - apply improverished autogen globally

2003-03-29 11:25  Josef Spillner <dr_maux@users.sourceforge.net>

	* m4/ggz.m4: - update GGZ macro file

2003-02-22 07:46  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/room.c: Don't segfault if the chat message is NULL.

2003-02-22 07:41  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/room.c: Send each line of a chat separately, breaking the
	message up around '\n' and sending a new <CHAT> tag for each line
	of the message.
	
	This means multi-line chats will generally work very well
	(consistent with IRC behavior, AFAICT).  A single line still can't
	be longer than the server's maximum length (which is enforced by
	the network code, via truncation).  And \r or \r\n line terminators
	will not be (properly) recognized.

2003-02-22 07:16  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: Truncate a chat message if it is longer than
	the server allows.

2003-02-22 06:40  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: Read the max chat length from the server more
	properly: including freeing the pointer when we're done with it,
	and using a better default value.

2003-02-16 13:59  Josef Spillner <dr_maux@users.sourceforge.net>

	* autogen.sh: - new autogen.sh

