	* ggzmod/: ggzmod.h, io.c: - Mark some char * strings as const char
	*.  - Pass a real pointer-to-integer to ggz_read_int; don't fake
	it.

2002-11-01 08:02  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: Add default error messages for the E_USR_LOOKUP
	and E_AT_TABLE chat error codes.

2002-11-01 06:35  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: ggzcore.h, server.c: Remove deprecated and unused
	function ggzcore_server_write_data().

2002-11-01 06:15  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: ggzcore.h, netxml.c, room.c, server.c: Change the error
	events (GGZ_LOGIN_FAIL, GGZ_ENTER_FAIL, GGZ_CHAT_FAIL,
	GGZ_TABLE_LAUNCH_FAIL) to pass a pointer to a GGZErrorEventData
	structure instead of just a pointer to a string.  This allows the
	frontend code to better handle the error.  Backwards-compatability
	is preserved by making the same string be the first field of the
	structure.

2002-10-31 03:18  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: Have _ggzcore_net_send_line return 0 (rather
	than the return value of write()) on success.  Some of the callers
	check directly against 0.

2002-10-30 07:51  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: ggzcore.h, net.h, netxml.c, server.c: Fix 'const char
	*' problems. (Apparently my config.h #defined 'const' away, so none
	of the problems were apparent before now.)

2002-10-30 04:33  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: Many micro-changes to the net code:   - Avoid
	bad things if the server sends us bad tags.    - Avoid memory leaks
	in several places when the server sends us	GOOD tags.    - A
	couple of comments on things that look wrong, but aren't.    - Make
	code more readible by removing excessive nested if's.

2002-10-29 12:30  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: - Read the <RESULT> code as a string, not a
	value.	- Also, handle _all_ error conditions for a CHAT result,
	not just   the few we suspect can happen.

2002-10-29 10:42  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: Remove 'joinspectator' and 'leavespectator'
	ACTIONs of the <UPDATE> tag.
	
	Connecting to an older ggzd should give the relative harmless side
	effect that spectators are invisible to you.

2002-10-29 07:05  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/ggzcore.h: Added documentation comments to all elements
	of ggzcore.
	
	Many of these are of the form:	 /** @brief Return the name of the
	player. */   char* ggzcore_player_get_name(GGZPlayer *player);
	
	but this is at least a start toward more complete documentation. 
	And since Doxygen may refuse to include any "undocumented" elements
	in its documentation at all, this may be a good thing even by
	itself.

2002-10-28 21:52  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/ggzcore.h: Some more documentation for ggzcore.

2002-10-28 07:03  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: ggzcore.h, netxml.c, player.c, player.h, room.c,
	room.h: - Add forfeits to the record.  - Change the stats retreival
	function: it returns a boolean indicating   whether there are any
	stats of that type.  - Add support for ratings, rankings, and
	highscores.  - Fix a bug whereby stats weren't updated when a
	player was added to a	room.

2002-10-28 06:08  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: "#define ATTR ggz_xmlelement_get_attr" makes
	this file a lot shorter and more readible.

2002-10-27 13:46  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: ggzcore.h, netxml.c, player.c, player.h, room.c,
	room.h: GGZCore support for player win-loss records, along with
	some unrelated net code cleanups.

2002-10-27 00:35  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: ggzcore.h, netxml.c, room.c, room.h: Added client
	support for the <JOIN> and <LEAVE> tags sent by the server.
	
	  <JOIN TABLE='5'/>
	  <LEAVE REASON='boot' PLAYER='jdorje'/>
	
	Now the client will no longer treat the <RESULT> tags (actions
	'join' and 'leave') as indications that the player has joined/left
	the table.  It will wait to see the appropriate <JOIN> or <LEAVE>
	tag.
	
	Core clients will only be slightly affected: there is now some
	useful event data for the GGZ_TABLE_JOIN and GGZ_TABLE_LEFT room
	events.
	
	The information sent by ggzd is not currently checked - we just
	change the GGZServer appropriately and then send it to the core
	client.  There's not much we could do anyway...
	
	Note that this change will break network compatabiliy.	Don't try
	to play a game on an older server!

2002-10-26 22:19  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: server.c, server.h: Trivial cleanups to server.[ch],
	including replacing some 'int' and '0' with 'GGZClientReqError' and
	'E_OK'.

2002-10-25 10:11  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzmod/ggzmod.c: After kill()ing the game client, wait() for it
	to die.  Thus we can avoid creating arbitrary defunct processees.

2002-10-24 11:56  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/ggzcore.h: More comments/documentation for ggzcore.

2002-10-24 09:17  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/ggzcore.h: Better documentation of the ggzcore server
	events.

2002-10-23 20:01  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: Correctly send the seat number for a SIT/MOVE
	to seat 0.

2002-10-22 22:17  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: game.c, net.h, netxml.c, protocol.h: Add handling for
	the SIT, STAND, and BOOT seat transactions.

2002-10-22 18:40  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: Add ggz__attribute to _ggzcore_net_send_line().

2002-10-22 06:25  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/game.c: Add handlers for all of the different ggzmod
	transactions.  Only the OPEN and BOT transaction is currently
	actually handled.

2002-10-22 06:24  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: When sending a table seat update, we need to
	include the number of seats at the table.

2002-10-22 03:03  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: ggzcore.h, room.c: Added function
	ggzcore_room_get_table_by_id().  Note that
	_ggzcore_room_get_table_by_id() already existed and is used
	extensively.

2002-10-22 02:39  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/room.c: More parameter checking in
	_ggzcore_room_join_table:   - Make sure we're joining a table in
	the current room.    - Make sure we know about the table we're
	trying to join.

2002-10-21 06:35  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/game.c: #include "ggzmod-ggz.h" where necessary.

2002-10-21 06:26  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzmod/: Makefile.am, ggzmod-ggz.h, ggzmod.c, ggzmod.h, io.c,
	io.h, mod.h, protocol.h: - Created new file ggzmod-ggz.h, where all
	interface that is GGZ-specific	 goes.	This way the library can be
	the same, but game developers won't   have to look at the (growing
	amount of) GGZ-specific portions.  - Moved ggzmod_set_module,
	ggzmod_set_player, ggzmod_set_seat,   ggzmod_set_spectator_seat
	into ggzmod-ggz.h.  - Added functions ggzmod_request_stand,
	ggzmod_request_sit,   ggzmod_request_boot, ggzmod_request_bot,
	ggzmod_request_open to	 ggzmod.h.  - Implemented the backend code
	so that if a transaction request function   is called by the game,
	the GGZ side of ggzmod will be told about it.  - Added the
	GGZModTransaction type, and a GGZdModTransactionHandler   function
	type for GGZ to use.  This allows the handling of transaction  
	requests to be kept separate from the code game developers need to
	see.  - When each transaction is requested by the game client, the
	appropriate   transaction handler will be called by the GGZ side of
	ggzmod.  Thus	ggzcore will be able to forward the requests to
	ggzd.

2002-10-21 03:21  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: If we receive a 'join' or 'leave' event from
	the server, handle any spectators that are received along with that
	event.	This is more intuitive than the 'joinspectator' and
	'leavespectator' events, and IMO should eventually replace them
	(however, changing this at the server will almost certainly break
	old clients).  So for now I've just enabled the client to handle
	it.

2002-10-20 00:29  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: netxml.c, room.c: Adjust for  the GGZ_CHAT_NONE ->
	GGZ_CHAT_UNKNOWN change, and improve handling of this chat type.

2002-10-18 08:23  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: game.c, game.h, ggzcore.h, netxml.c, table.c, table.h:
	Extensive changes so that spectator seats should now completely
	work at the client end: - When the server sends a <SPECTATOR> tag,
	track the list of spectators   separately from the list of seats. 
	Doing otherwise will only invite   trouble.  - When we change a
	spectator seat for the table (GGZTable), change it for	 the game
	(GGZGame) as well if appropriate.  - When we set the table
	associated with a game, send the current spectator   list to the
	game client.

2002-10-18 01:56  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: conf.c, game.c, game.h, gametype.c, ggz-config.c,
	ggzcore.h, hook.c, hook.h, init.c, module.c, net.h, netxml.c,
	player.c, player.h, room.c, room.h, server.c, server.h, state.c,
	table.c: Cleaned up #includes in ggzcore:   - Make sure #include
	<config.h> is in every .c file.  (Note that	the autoconf manual
	says <config.h> should be used insteead of     "config.h".)   - Do
	#include "ggzcore.h" instead of #include <ggzcore.h>.	 -
	Miscellaneous reordering of #includes.

2002-10-17 23:23  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: #include <fcntl.h> instead of <sys/fcntl.h>,
	since that's where open() is.

2002-10-17 01:59  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/game.c: To find the table with a given ID#, call
	_ggzcore_room_get_table_by_id, not ggzcore_room_get_nth_table. 
	This fixes a guaranteed segfault when the tables are unordered (but
	other errors may still be possible).

2002-10-16 02:07  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* acinclude.ggz: Improvement (hopefully :-) to acinclude.ggz.  Now
	each GGZ check takes two optional parameters.  For instance:
	
	  AC_GGZ_LIBGGZ(action-if-found, action-if-not-found)
	
	'action-if-found' will be evaluated if the specified module was
	found.	'action-if-not-found' will be evaluated if the module is
	not found.  This is consistent with other autoconf macros.  If
	'action-is-not-found' is empty, then an error will be emitted if
	the module isn't found.  If 'action-if-not-found' is "ignore", then
	the module will simply be ignored if it's not found.
	
	This is not entirely backwards-compatible, since "ignore" used to
	be the first parameter to the macro.  But this way is more
	consistent, in my opinion.

2002-10-15 03:57  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzmod/: ggzmod.c, io.c: Fixes to seat, spectator seat, and
	player naming (string handling) in ggzmod.

2002-10-15 03:39  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzmod/: ggzmod.c, io.c, io.h, mod.h: Cleanup to ggzmod's launch
	code.

2002-10-15 00:08  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: game.c, game.h, ggzcore.h, room.c, server.c, server.h,
	table.c: Changes to ggzcore to send GGZ data to the game client
	through ggzmod.
	
	One protocol change was required: the ggzcore_game_init() function
	now takes as an additional parameter the GGZServer* server
	variable.  I also removed the obsolete function ggzcore_game_join.
	
	However, the way ggzcore is structured is not ideal for having the
	GGZ information be communicated to the game table.  Currently when
	the game launch is done, the player's name is known and we know if
	they are spectating.  But we will not generally know the player's
	seat number (which is assigned by ggzd and sent back to us later)
	or what the other seats at the table are (we may know if we join a
	table, but not if we launch one).  In fact if the client calls the
	functions ggzcore_room_join_table and ggzcore_game_launch out of
	order, we might not even know this bit of information at the time
	the game client is launched.
	
	The solution to these problems may involve cleaning up ggzcore and
	changing the API some more.

2002-10-14 23:59  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzmod/: ggzmod.c, ggzmod.h, io.c, io.h, mod.h: Improvements to
	the API after realizing I'd forgotten something:   - The player's
	name is included with the player (our player) data.    - Renamed
	ggzmod_[get|set]_my_seat as ggzmod_[get|set]_player.

2002-10-14 22:22  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzmod/: ggzmod.c, ggzmod.h, io.c, io.h, mod.h, protocol.h:
	Extensive additions to ggzmod to allow game clients to access
	information about the current player and the table.
	
	Additions: - New seat events:	- GGZMOD_EVENT_PLAYER: when we get
	information about us (current player)	- GGZMOD_EVENT_SEAT: when a
	seat changes   - GGZMOD_EVENT_SPECTATOR_SEAT: when a spectator seat
	changes - New structures GGZSeat and GGZSpectatorSeat; similar to
	what ggzdmod   uses.  - New functions for game:
	ggzmod_get_num_seats, ggzmod_get_seat,	
	ggzmod_get_num_spectator_seats, ggzmod_get_spectator_seat,  
	ggzmod_get_my_seat.  - New functions for GGZ: ggzmod_set_my_seat,
	ggzmod_set_seat,   ggzmod_set_spectator_seat.  Conspicuously absent
	are ggzmod_set_num_seats   and ggzmod_set_num_spectator_seats. 
	Yay.

2002-10-10 22:55  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/netxml.c: Correctly handle a table chat (GGZ_CHAT_TABLE)
	if we receive it from the server.

2002-10-10 19:08  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* configure.in, ggzcore/Doxyfile: Bumped version numbers to
	0.0.7pre.

2002-10-10 14:41  Josef Spillner <dr_maux@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/conf.c: - allow for consecutive calls of
	ggzcore_conf_initialize - this overrides previous calls, and thus
	enables on-the-fly configuration   changes

2002-10-10 00:56  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: ggzcore.h, room.c: Remove the GGZ_CHAT, GGZ_ANNOUNCE,
	GGZ_PRVMSG, and GGZ_BEEP ggzcore room events.  These are all merged
	into GGZ_CHAT_EVENT.  The associated event data is now a
	GGZChatEventData*.
	
	This will reduce the amount of code necessary to handle chat
	messages in virtually all modules, and make adding new chat types
	significantly easier.

2002-10-09 01:32  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* ggzcore/: ggzcore.h, net.h, netxml.c, room.c, room.h: - Move
	GGZChatType enum into ggz_common.  - Add ggz_chattype_to_string()
	and ggz_string_to_chattype functions to   ggz_common.  - Change
	existing code to use the above two instead of their own custom	
	code.  - Don't accept invalid and dangerous chat messages (sent
	across the   network).	But do accept invalid and non-dangerous
	chat messages: to   improve backward-compatability if new chat
	types are added.

2002-10-07 23:28  Jason Short <jdorje@users.sourceforge.net>

	* NEWS: Rewrote NEWS for 0.0.6, and propogated it to all modules.

